peopleAlsoAsk.question: Do old tins have value?

peopleAlsoAsk.question: What year did tin toys come out?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: Tin toys were first made in the United States in the early 1830s. By the 1860s, many U.S. companies were producing the toys. In fact, the years from 1865 to 1895 are called the "Golden Age of American Tin Toys." By the 1890s, German and French toymakers were realizing that tin toys were popular in the United States.
